WEBVTT

00:09:58.527 --> 00:10:00.260
also differed from my own.

00:10:00.749 --> 00:10:03.825
And I found that his understanding
of issues like welfare

00:10:03.849 --> 00:10:05.043
and affirmative action

00:10:05.067 --> 00:10:07.188
was tied and deeply rooted

00:10:07.212 --> 00:10:11.299
in his understanding of various
libertarian and conservative beliefs,

00:10:11.323 --> 00:10:14.879
what diminishes and increases
their presence in our society.

00:10:15.535 --> 00:10:18.582
While he expressed
his viewpoints eloquently,

00:10:18.606 --> 00:10:20.485
I remained thoroughly unconvinced.

00:10:20.923 --> 00:10:23.910
But I did walk away
with a deeper understanding.

00:10:24.796 --> 00:10:26.262
It's my belief

00:10:27.134 --> 00:10:29.921
that to achieve progress
in the face of adversity,